# Cursor Rules for Professional Marketing Consultant Website

# Project Overview
# This is a professional marketing consultant website that should reflect:
# - Trust and credibility
# - Modern, clean design
# - Conversion-focused user experience
# - SEO best practices
# - Mobile-first responsive design

# File Structure Rules
ignore:
  - node_modules/
  - .git/
  - .DS_Store
  - *.log
  - dist/
  - build/
  - .env.local
  - .env.production
  - .next/
  - .vercel/
  - coverage/
  - .nyc_output/

# Allowed file types for editing
allow:
  - src/
  - public/
  - components/
  - pages/
  - styles/
  - assets/
  - content/
  - config/
  - utils/
  - hooks/
  - types/
  - tests/

# Code Style Guidelines
style:
  # Use modern JavaScript/TypeScript features
  - Use ES6+ syntax and async/await
  - Prefer functional components with hooks
  - Use TypeScript for type safety
  - Follow consistent naming conventions (camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components)
  
  # CSS/SCSS guidelines
  - Use CSS modules or styled-components for styling
  - Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach
  - Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for layouts
  - Maintain consistent spacing and typography scales
  
  # React/Next.js best practices
  - Use Next.js App Router or Pages Router consistently
  - Implement proper SEO with meta tags and structured data
  - Use Image component for optimized images
  - Implement proper loading states and error boundaries

# Marketing Website Specific Rules
marketing:
  # Content guidelines
  - Focus on benefits over features
  - Use clear, compelling headlines
  - Include social proof elements (testimonials, case studies)
  - Implement clear call-to-action buttons
  - Use persuasive copywriting techniques
  
  # User experience
  - Ensure fast loading times (< 3 seconds)
  - Implement intuitive navigation
  - Use clear visual hierarchy
  - Include contact forms and lead capture
  - Optimize for conversion funnels
  
  # SEO requirements
  - Use semantic HTML structure
  - Implement proper heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3)
  - Include alt text for all images
  - Use descriptive URLs and meta descriptions
  - Implement schema markup for local business

# Design System Guidelines
design:
  # Color palette (professional marketing consultant)
  - Primary: Professional blues (#1e40af, #3b82f6)
  - Secondary: Trust greens (#059669, #10b981)
  - Accent: Warm oranges (#ea580c, #f97316)
  - Neutral: Grays (#f8fafc, #e2e8f0, #64748b, #1e293b)
  
  # Typography
  - Headings: Modern sans-serif (Inter, Poppins, or similar)
  - Body: Readable sans-serif (Inter, Open Sans, or similar)
  - Use consistent font weights and sizes
  
  # Spacing
  - Use consistent spacing scale (4px, 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px, 64px)
  - Maintain proper whitespace for readability
  
  # Components
  - Buttons: Rounded corners, hover effects, clear hierarchy
  - Cards: Subtle shadows, rounded corners, proper padding
  - Forms: Clear labels, validation states, accessible design

# Performance Requirements
performance:
  - Optimize images (WebP format, proper sizing)
  - Minimize bundle size
  - Implement lazy loading
  - Use CDN for static assets
  - Enable compression and caching

# Accessibility Standards
accessibility:
  - WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
  - Proper ARIA labels
  - Keyboard navigation support
  - Color contrast ratios
  - Screen reader compatibility
  - Focus indicators

# Security Guidelines
security:
  - Sanitize user inputs
  - Use HTTPS only
  - Implement proper form validation
  - Secure API endpoints
  - Protect against XSS and CSRF attacks

# Testing Requirements
testing:
  - Unit tests for utility functions
  - Component tests for UI elements
  - Integration tests for user flows
  - E2E tests for critical paths
  - Cross-browser compatibility testing

# Content Management
content:
  - Use markdown or CMS for content management
  - Implement proper content structure
  - Include blog/news section for SEO
  - Regular content updates
  - Localization support if needed

# Analytics and Tracking
analytics:
  - Google Analytics 4 implementation
  - Conversion tracking setup
  - Heat mapping tools (Hotjar, etc.)
  - A/B testing capabilities
  - Performance monitoring

# Deployment and Hosting
deployment:
  - Use Vercel, Netlify, or similar modern hosting
  - Implement CI/CD pipeline
  - Environment variable management
  - Backup and recovery procedures
  - Monitoring and alerting

# Code Quality
quality:
  - Use ESLint and Prettier
  - Implement pre-commit hooks
  - Code review process
  - Documentation requirements
  - Performance monitoring

# Specific Marketing Consultant Features
features:
  - Service showcase with detailed descriptions
  - Client testimonials and case studies
  - Portfolio of successful campaigns
  - Contact forms with lead qualification
  - Blog with marketing insights
  - Social media integration
  - Newsletter signup
  - Appointment booking system
  - Pricing packages (if applicable)
  - About page with credentials
  - FAQ section
  - Resources/downloads section

# File Naming Conventions
naming:
  - Components: PascalCase (e.g., HeroSection.tsx)
  - Pages: kebab-case (e.g., about-us.tsx)
  - Utilities: camelCase (e.g., formatDate.ts)
  - Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., API_ENDPOINTS.ts)
  - CSS modules: camelCase (e.g., heroSection.module.css)

# Comments and Documentation
documentation:
  - Use JSDoc for function documentation
  - Include README files for major components
  - Document API endpoints
  - Maintain changelog
  - Include setup instructions

# Git Workflow
git:
  - Use conventional commits
  - Feature branch workflow
  - Pull request reviews
  - Semantic versioning
  - Automated testing on PRs
